---
import { SelectDemo } from '../../components/form-control-demos';
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Select" description="Groundwork select component">
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Select</h1>
        <p>Use Select when the user must choose one option from a short, known list.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">When to use</h2>
        <p>Use Select inside Field so the label, hint, error copy, and ARIA relationships stay consistent with other form controls.</p>
        <p>Include a clear empty option such as “Select a country” when there is no safe default.</p>
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">When not to use</h2>
        <p>Do not use Select for a very small set of prominent choices where radio buttons would be easier to scan. Do not use it for long searchable datasets; build a dedicated autocomplete pattern instead.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Demo</h2>
        <SelectDemo />
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card gw-stack">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Accessibility notes</h2>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Select requires an accessible name through <code class="gw-mono">aria-label</code> or <code class="gw-mono">aria-labelledby</code>. Prefer using Field to provide the visible label and ARIA wiring.</p>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Keep option labels short and specific. The selected value should make sense when read with the field label.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
